20.3 Changing common ssh server options

server options are set in /etc/ssh/sshd_config
	port 22 - default port
	permitrootlogin - allow root user to log in with ssh?
	pubkeyauthentication - is public key auth allowed?
	passwordauthentication
	x11forwarding - allows graphical screen forwarding
	AllowUsers useraccount - allows only certain users to ssh in
	
	
client options are set in /etc/ssh/ssh_config
	to apply changes, systemctl restart sshd